INSERT INTO activities VALUES (1,'<P>\r\nANG PARTY-LIST ELECTIONS\r\n<P>\r\nAlinsunod sa itinatadhana ng Konstitusyon at ng Republic Act 7941, ipinatupad ang party-list election sa bansa noong nakaraang Mayo 11, 1998. \r\n<P> \r\nLayunin ng party-list system na magkaroon ng pagkakataon ang maliliit na partido na kumakatawan sa mga tinatawag na \"marginalized\" at \"underrepresented\" na sektor gaya ng manggagawa, magsasaka, maralitang lungsod, kababaihan, atbp. na magkaroon ng representasyon sa Kongreso. \r\nDalawampung porsyento (20%) ng kabuuang pwesto sa Kongreso ay inilaan sa party-list system. Noong 1998, 14 lang sa dapat ay 52 nakalaang pwesto ang nakuha ng 13  party-list organizations.  Isa sa mga nanalo ang Sanlakas.\r\n<P>\r\nAng isang party-list organization ay makakakuha ng isang pwesto kung makakalikom ito ng minimum na 2% ng kabuuang boto sa party-list. Bawat partido ay pinapayagang makakuha ng maksimum na tatlong (3) pwesto.\r\nHalimbawa: Kung ang kabuuang boto sa party-list ay umabot ng 20 milyon, ang isang partido ay dapat makakuha ng 400,000 boto para makakuha ng isang pwesto, 800,000 sa dalawang pwesto at 1.2 milyon sa tatlong pwesto. \r\n<P>\r\nSa party-list system, ang ibinoboto  ay partido, hindi tao.\r\n<P>\r\nHalimbawa, sa balota:\r\n<P>\r\nSenator: Maria <BR>\r\nDistrict Representative: Juan <BR>\r\nParty-List Representative: SANLAKAS <BR>\r\n<P>\r\nKaya\'t tandaan, ngayong eleksyon, dalawa ang ating iboboto sa Kongreso. Isang District Representative at isang Party-List Representative.\r\n\r\n<P>\r\n----------------------------------------- <BR>\r\n\r\nfrom the SANLAKAS PUBLIC INFORMATION BUREAU <BR>\r\n\r\n<P>\r\n************ POSTSCRIPTS *********** <BR>\r\n<P>\r\nPS1: Want to be included in our mailing list for current press releases?  Reply to dis msg.\r\n<P>\r\nPS2. Feel free to pass this msg as we want more people to know about the party-list system\r\n<P>\r\nPS3. Also, an allied party-list group, the PARTIDO NG MANGGAGAWA is now on the web. http://www.manggagawa.cjb.net\r\n<P>\r\nPS4. Also, see Tributes and Eulogies for slain labor leader Ka Popoy Lagman ---> http://www.popoy.cjb.net</PRE>','2001-05-14',635,0,0,0,'Y','E-mail sent to info@vote.ph (4/17)','info on Party-List Elections',20010417235237);
INSERT INTO activities VALUES (3,'<PRE>\r\nFrom:  Simbahang Lingkod ng Bayan <slb@admu.edu.ph>\r\nDate:  Wed Apr 18, 2001 6:23am\r\nSubject:  Namfrel Volunteers Needed\r\n\r\nDear Friends,\r\n\r\nThere is less than one month before the May 14 National Elections.\r\n\r\nThe National Movement for Free Elections has finally been given the\r\nmandate the to conduct its OPERATION QUICK COUNT based of the official\r\nsixth copy of the Precinct Election Return (based on Comelec Resolution\r\nSPP No. 00-040 dated 05 April 2001).\r\n\r\nBecause of the delays caused by opposition to NAMFREL\'s accrediation\r\nby ceratin interest blocks, our preparation have been extremely\r\nlimited and delayed.\r\n\r\nWe are in urgent need of volunteers, logistics and donations.  We are\r\nhandling NAMFREL Quezon City covering more than one million votes in\r\nfour districts.  Quezon City has the greatest number of voters of any\r\nmunicipality, city or province.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested to volunteer as a voting center manager, precinct\r\nvolunteer or data courier to help gather the base data from Quezon City\'s\r\nmore than 5000 precincts from 3PM May 14 to 9AM May 15.\r\n\r\nPlease write to ramirez@i-manila.com.ph. If you are interested to\r\ndonate to the effort, please contact Raymund Magadaluyo at 0917-\r\n8326861 or Rissa Ramos pframos@pacific.net.ph.\r\n\r\nWe shall have a volunteer training seminar on Satruday, April 21,\r\nfrom 9AM to 12NN at the Ateneo College Campus, Loyola Hts. Quezon\r\nCity.\r\n\r\nWE URGENTLY NEED YOUR HELP. WE ARE VERY SHORT ON VOLUNTEERS AND\r\nLOGISTICS.  YOU NEED NOT BE FROM QUEZON CITY TO VOLUNTEER OR SUPPORT\r\nOUR EFFORTS.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you. For God and country.\r\n\r\nPlease pass this on to friends and relatives.\r\n\r\n\r\nJoval Pantangco\r\nNAMFREL CO-CHAIRPERSON\r\nQUEZON CITY\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n****************************************************************************\r\n****\r\n      For questions and suggestions, write us:\r\n\r\n          SIMBAHANG LINGKOD NG BAYAN\r\n        Loyola House of Studies\r\n          Ateneo de Manila University\r\n\r\nTel. No.  426-6101 local 3440/3441 Mailing Address:\r\n    0917-499-2032   P.O. Box 257, UP Post Office\r\nTelefax:  426-5968   1144 Quezon City, Philippines\r\n</PRE>','2001-05-14',650,0,0,5,'N','E-mail from PH-Cyberview (4/18)','Namfrel Volunteers Needed',20010419155453);
INSERT INTO activities VALUES (4,'[Source: E-mail sent to: info@vote.ph by Michael P. Garay (manggagawa@edsamail.com.ph)]<BR>\r\n<P>\r\n*******************************************<BR>\r\nNEWS RELEASE<BR>\r\nApril 24, 2001<BR>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<P>\r\nLocal leader of PM killed\r\n<P>\r\nAt around 7:00 last night, two gunmen shot and killed Manuel Ibe, president of the 1,300-strong labor union of Liwayway Manufacturing and founding member of labor party-list group Partido ng Manggagawa (PM) chapter in Cavite. He was slain in front of the factory gates in Imus as he was going home from work.\r\n<P>\r\nIbe is a leader of PM in Cavite and was a prominent figure in the group\'s successful province-wide motorcade and chapter founding assembly last Sunday. He is the second leader of the PM to be slain in almost three months, following the assassination of militant labor leader Ka Popoy Lagman last February 6. \r\n<P>\r\nThe group\'s Cavite chapter announced that it will launch mass actions to demand the immediate capture of the suspects and the swift resolution of the murder case.\r\n<P>\r\nAccording to PM national chairman Renato Magtubo, \"The perpetrators of this grisly act are undoubtedly enemies of the working class. Dark and sinister forces want to derail the PM as they are threatened by labor\'s active participation in mainstream politics.\r\n<P>\r\n\"While the slaying of Ka Popoy was meant to intimidate the PM, which was then in the heat of preparation for its National Founding Congress, the murder of Manuel Ibe intends to terrorize the PM Cavite chapter after its successful founding assembly.\"\r\n<P>\r\nMagtubo added, \"However, we will not be cowed. The party will persevere on its aims and objectives.\"\r\n<P>\r\nHe said, \"With barely a few days before Labor Day, militant labor leaders who sincerely strive for the interest of the working class in the parliamentary arena face the iron hand of repression and harassment. If government continuously fails to address this, labor will be forced to struggle through non-parliamentary means.\"\r\n<P>\r\nThe group decried the \"evolving pattern of repression against the PM\". Early this month, Reynaldo Lopez, PM organizer for Cavite was arrested. He was released after 3 days of incarceration. ###\r\n<P>\r\n\r\nPARTIDO NG MANGGAGAWA ONLINE: http://www.manggagawa.cjb.net\r\n<BR><BR><BR>','2001-05-01',605,28,0,0,'N','Email sent to info@vote.ph (4/24)','Murder of PM local leader',20010424163523);
INSERT INTO activities VALUES (5,'[Source: E-mail from Harvey S. Keh (hskeh@admu.edu.ph) to AAXS-Whazzup Mailing List]<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<PRE>\r\nDear Friend,\r\n\r\n\r\nAs most of you probably know by now, the Office of Student\r\nActivities (OSA) of the Ateneo de Manila University is currently \r\nspearheading the Quezon City NAMFREL Operation Quick Count (OQC) for \r\nthis coming May 14 elections. It is through this OQC that we hope to \r\nbe able to contribute to the development of our country through an \r\nhonest and clean elections.\r\n\r\nThus, we would like to ask for your support in two possible \r\nways. Firstly, you can opt to help us out by volunteering your time \r\nto the OQC center, the OQC will start late night of May 14 until May \r\n20. Shifts will be on a 4-hour basis and the OQC Center will be \r\nrunning for 24 hours. Secondly, you can help us out by donating or \r\nlending us out supplies that we could use for our OQC. Below are some \r\nof the things which you can give or lend us:\r\n\r\na.) Money (any amount will really go a long way)\r\nb.) Two-way Radios\r\nc.) Food (Sandwiches, etc.)\r\nd.) Drinks (Water, Juices, etc.)\r\ne.) Calculators\r\nf.) Flashlights\r\ng.) Pentel Pens\r\nh.) Pens and Pencils\r\ni.) Mats (\"Banigs\")\r\nj.) Manila Paper/s\r\nk.) First Aid Kit/s\r\n\r\nThese are just some of the ways by which you can help us out. \r\nyou can start giving in you donations at the Office of Student \r\nActivities (OSA), Colayco Hall. Rest assured, that we will take care \r\nof the things that we will borrow from you and will return it as soon \r\nas we finish our OQC operations.\r\n\r\nShould you decide to volunteer, please feel free to send your\r\ncomplete name and contact numbers to namfrelvolunteers@hotmail.com . \r\nIf you have any questions, please feel free to call us at 426-6001 \r\nloc. 5050 or 5051.\r\n\r\nPlease pass this message to your family, friends and people \r\nyou know who may be interested to help us out.\r\n\r\nThanks so much! Have a nice day! :)\r\n\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nHarvey S. Keh\r\nOQC Chairperson\r\nNAMFREL-Quezon City\r\nXS \'96 ADMU \'00\r\n</PRE>','2001-05-20',650,0,0,5,'N','E-mail from AAXS-Whazzup (4/24)','Namfrel 2001 Call for Donation',20010424164548);
INSERT INTO activities VALUES (6,'<P>\r\nSTATEMENT on the pro-Estrada \"Edsa 3\"<BR>\r\n27 April 2001<BR>\r\nSANLAKAS<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nKAPANGYARIHAN PARA SA MASA,<BR>\r\nHINDI KAY ERAP O GLORIA!<BR>\r\n<P>\r\n    Ang Sanlakas ay nananawagan sa mga kapatid naming maralita - kung ilulunsad natin ang Edsa 3, ito ay dapat para sa ating mahihirap hindi pa para kay Erap. Kung totohanang ilulunsad ng mahihirap ang Edsa 3, gawin natin ito para sa ating sariling interes at hindi para maibalik lang si Erap sa poder. \r\n<P>\r\n    Sa mga kapatid naming maralita, huwag nating hatiiin ang ating hanay sa pagitan ng pro-Gloria o pro-Erap. Tayo ay pare-pareho ng kapalaran bilang mahihirap. Pero kami ay naniniwala na ang ating katubusan ay wala kay Gloria o kay Erap. \r\n<P>\r\n    Maaring pareho ang ating damdamin na binigo ng dalawang Edsa ang mga mithiin ng mahihirap. Kami sa Sanlakas ay di rin kuntento na ang resulta ng Edsa Dos ay pag-akyat lang sa poder ni Gloria. Pero ang maglunsad ng Edsa 3 para lamang ibalik si Erap ay mas malaking trahedya. Si Erap ay nagkasala at dapat lang humarap sa hustisya.\r\n<P>\r\n    Kayat huwag nating ulitin sa ikatlong pagkakataon ang pagkakamali ng dalawang Edsa. Sa halip, hinangin natin ang pagkakaisa sa pagitan nating mahihirap para ipaglaban ang ating sariling interes - ang kapakanan ng mga mahihirap. Sa ganitong paraan, mas posible ang pagbabago kaysa manatili tayo sa pagpanig sa pagitan ni Erap at ni Gloria.  \r\n<P>\r\n    Kung gusto natin ng pababago, dapat nagkakaisa tayong kumilos para baguhin ang sistema ng ating bansa - ang pulitika sa ating bayan. Dapat nating likhain ang sariling lakas at kilusan laban sa lahat ng trapo sa ating bansa. Ang kapangyarihan ay dapat hawak nating mahihirap hindi ng mga gaya ni Gloria at ni Erap.\r\n<P>\r\n    Nananawagan din kami sa pamahalaan na huwag gumamit ng dahas sa protestang nagaganap sa Edsa. Karapatan ng mamamayan na maglunsad ng ganitong protesta, anuman ang kanilang paniniwala. \r\n<P>\r\n    Sa huli ay nagbibigay din kami ng babala kay Gloria na huwag balewalain ang namumuong daluyong ng masa sila man ay pro-Erap. Naniniwala kami na bukod sa kanilang simpatiya sa kanilang idolo ay naroon sa kanilang damdamin ang paghahanap ng totoong pagbabago.(30)\r\n<BR>\r\n<BR>','2001-05-05',635,0,0,0,'Y','E-mail sent to info@vote.ph (4/29)','Kapangyarihan sa Masa ….',20010430080529);
INSERT INTO activities VALUES (7,'<PRE>\r\nFrom: Teresita C Dumana [mailto:tcdumana@edsamail.com.ph]\r\nSent: Friday, May 11, 2001 8:47 AM\r\nTo: elagda-makati@yahoogroups.com\r\nCc: anadelfierro@hotmail.com; darryl_dj@usa.net;\r\nsharivell@edsamail.com.ph; adonisd@hotmail.com\r\nSubject: [eLagda-Makati] REMINDERS/GUIDELINES FOR NAMFREL VOLUNTEERS\r\n\r\nhi guys,\r\n\r\n3 days to D-Day. \r\n\r\ni know i\'m supposed to give you your\r\nassignments  -- that is,precincts and\r\npolling centers (schools) -- but as of \r\n5 pm yesterday(10 may),the principals of the 3\r\nschools could not give me their precinct\r\nlayout, upon which i will base our deployment\r\nplan. i am told i\'ll get it today. \r\n\r\nto reiterate: you will be assigned to any of 3\r\nschools in san antonio village, makati.SAV is bounded\r\non the south by buendia ave, on the east by kamagong, \r\non the west by mayapis and on the north by vito cruz.\r\nhere are the schools and their location:\r\n\r\n1. pamantasan ng makati  -- corner buendia, mayapis and\r\n   malugay, with the entrance on malugay (behind buendia).\r\n   \r\n   VOTING CENTER MANAGERS: TESS DUMANA (CP: 0917-8312623)\r\n   \r\n                           JOJO VICENCIO (CP: 0917-7633000)\r\n   \r\n2. makati high school annex -- mayapis st., about 3 blocks\r\n   from pamantasan ng makati (going inward to SAV)\r\n \r\n   VCM: CELY DIZON (will get her cell # later)\r\n\r\n3. san antonio elementary school -- corner caong and lumbayao,\r\n   a block, westward, from makati high school\r\n\r\n   VCM: REY GARCIA (CP: 0919-5883011)\r\n\r\n\r\nURGENT REQUESTS:\r\n\r\n1. please send me, by private email, fax(8977671), phone 8963201,\r\n   or txt msg (0917-8312623), the following:\r\n\r\n   a. your given name (i already have your nicknames). this is for\r\n      the insurance for volunteers (yes, we are insured for the\r\n      princely sum of P50,000!) oh, well, we were going to serve,\r\n      anyway, even without insurance...\r\n\r\n   b. your residence phone no. so i can call you, if necessary,\r\n      over the weekend\r\n\r\n   c. please enter my cell phone no. in your fon books so you \r\n      wont keep asking me to ID myself. later, when you are given\r\n      your school/precinct assignments, please enter the cell #\r\n      of your respective VCMs too\r\n\r\n2. don\'t forget to make a TRANSPARENT PLASTIC JACKET for the\r\n   namfrel ID, with provisions for hanging around your neck. this \r\n   is VERRY IMPORTANT as it\'s the only way to ensure that the ID,\r\n   which you will need to claim the PRECIOUS 6TH COPY OF THE\r\n   ELECTION RETURNS, won\'t get lost.\r\n\r\n\r\nTHINGS TO BRING:\r\n\r\n1. your cell phone -- fully charged, w/ an extra battery if you have one\r\n2. flashlight\r\n3. a fan\r\n4. bottld water\r\n5. pen & paper\r\n6. black pentel pen (for printing your name on the ID card)\r\n7. face towel\r\n8. tissue (facial or otherwise)\r\n9. loaded camera, with flash\r\n10.and FOOD, glorious FOOD!\r\n   (i\'m sorry about this. i know i had earlier said that we shall\r\n   be given packed supper, but tony esteban (the namfrel-makati chair)\r\n   says funds are low this time and the best they can do is to send\r\n   sandwiches. i have, however, been able to ask for packed supper for\r\n   our group from chowking (a client of mine), so we\'ll have a full\r\n   meal for supper. we can save the namfrel sandwich for midnight\r\n   snack or something. however, PLEASE FEEL FREE TO BRING YOUR OWN FOOD,\r\n   PLUS SOME CANDY, CRACKERS, OR WHATEVER)\r\n\r\n   i also asked for bottled water to go with the packed supper from \r\n   chowking. i thought it better than soft drinks (hope no one minds)\r\n\r\n11. PLASTIC JACKET for ID (kulit, no?)\r\n\r\ni hope, PRAY, that no one will back out now. am grateful for the new recruits that some of you have referred to me. i truly hope no one will\r\nget intimidated by rumors/news of bomb threats. methinks we\'re made of sterner stuff....\r\n\r\nlet\'s pray that his political exercise will help move our country forward, as it should. (hope our candidates win, too!)\r\n\r\n\r\nKEEP THIS IN MIND, please:\r\n\r\n     NAMFREL\'S MANDATE IS TO DO A QUICK COUNT.\r\n     THE NAMFREL COUNT WILL BE BEASED ON OFFICIAL\r\n          ELECTION RETURNS GATHERED FROM THE PRECINCTS.\r\n     THE NAMFREL FIELD VOLUNTEERS (that\'s us)  JOB IS\r\n          TO SECURE THE 6TH COPY OF THE ELECTION RETURNS\r\n          FROM THE BOARD OF ELECTION INSPECTORS (the teachers\r\n          who man the precincts), MAKE SURE THE ENTRIES ARE\r\n          LEGIBLE and ACCURATE, and TO SUBMIT THE DOCUMENT\r\n          TO THE VOTING CENTER MANAGER (tess, jojo, cely or rey).\r\n     THE Board of Election Inspectors (BEI) WILL GIVE THE 6TH COPY\r\n          of the election returns ONLY TO THE AUTHORIZED NAMFREL\r\n          VOLUNTEER. \r\n      We shall be identified by our ID cards -- so pleeeeeaaase\r\n      GUARD THAT ID WITH YOUR LIFE!\r\n\r\n      VOTE EARLY SO YOU CAN RUN TO MAKATI IN THE PM.\r\n      WE SHOULD ALL BE AT OUR RESPECTIVE POSTS NO LATER THAN 2 PM.\r\n\r\n      \r\nplease call/fax/text me for any questions/concerns you might have.\r\n\r\nthanks to high heavens to all of you\r\nand God bless!\r\n\r\ntess\r\n\r\n</PRE>','2001-05-18',650,0,0,9,'N','E-mail from Elagda-Makati (5/11)','Reminders/Guidelines for NAMFREL Volunteers',20010511141038);
