INSERT INTO party VALUES (513,'Alternative Action','AA',0,'Y',0,2,0,0,'[Source:  brochureIT.doc brochure sent to info@vote.ph by Alexander E. Casiple]<BR><BR>\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that people power phenomenon in Edsa2 is a rejection of old politics which is based on wealth and violence.  That historical event resembles our new politics which is based on knowledge and information.  \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that the spontaneity of the Edsa  people power can be elevated into a higher form – more organized and institutionalized nationwide- that shall allow for broader ownership, wider participation, sharpening of its perspectives  in reaping and protecting its gains and even creating new victories.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that the youth and students armed with means to rapid information exchanges between them, represented the most formidable force in Edsa2.   \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe the same truth will hold to a knowledge-based New Politics we profess as it evolves into its higher form. \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that the hope of sustaining the gains of Edsa2 lies mainly on the youth and students who are advocates of the principles of New Politics.  \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that Edsa 2 is a manifestation of the first Edsa’s  strength and shortcoming.  Strength in the sense that power mainly based on knowledge and information was revalidated as potent enough to oust even a popularly elected, well entrenched but corrupt government.  A shortcoming in the sense that Edsa 1  failed to address the ensuing complacency and apathy  of people especially the youth who seemingly fell into slumber after a euphoric victory – thus allowing the rise to power of an incompetent government. \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe, that more than ever, the current reality is akin to a knowledge-based and Information Technology enabled politics, with the youth as its pillar and bridgehead.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that in the immediate future, knowledge and information shall represent the most important resource of the new system of wealth creation in the unfolding new economy.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that in the new economy, People’s access to information technology is as important as providing them access to other factors of production like, land, raw material and capital.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe again that the youth shall play a very important role for our country ‘s effective participation in the highly competitive and connected world with a so called digital economy. \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that the youth possesses the greatest  potential to effectively steer societies and small economies in transition,  (like cooperatives and other grassroots-based enterprises) to the new economic order.\r\n<P> \r\nWe believe that the youth in a conducive environment, shall serve as a well-spring of novel business ideas and shall  play the role of an accelerator in the new economy where speed and innovation is of prime importance. \r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that the youth especially the students, being a pulsating sector, is in the best position to bring the benefit of the new economy in general and information technology in particular, to the grassroots level, thus, narrowing  the Digital Divide.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that with a favorable environment,  the youth can immediately emulate the “learn and earn” opportunities in the knowledge-based new economy turning campuses into one of its  building block.\r\n<P>\r\nWe believe that, today and more true than ever in this country’s history, the youth indeed, is the hope of the fatherland.','[Source:  brochureIT.doc brochure sent to info@vote.ph by Alexander E. Casiple]<BR><BR>\r\n<P>\r\nALTERNATIVE ACTION is a newly formed partylist organization.  It is supported by former leading youth activists who worked with the poverty stricken people, listened to their cries and felt their pains. Like the proverbial wave, activists are deeply immersed (within the grassroots) when the sea is calm but rise to heights when there is storm.  With today’s realities, the activists are ready to rise once again to new heights as the strong wind of change is blustering the country. \r\n<P>\r\nThe birthing of ALTERNATIVE ACTION came amidst a social condition where CHANGE in the economic and political arena was so rapid that while it offers rich opportunities it is also loaded with dangers to humanity, our country, our organizations and ourselves. \r\n<P>\r\nWith the swiftness of change, the compression of the three\r\ndimensions of time: past, present, and the future is transpiring in ALTERNATIVE ACTION.  Drawing inspiration from the past, ALTERNATIVE ACTION relives the wisdom, dedication, creativity, fervor, passion and selflessness of former youth activists.  With in ALTERNATIVE ACTION, such attributes are being relevantly imbued to the effort of all parties especially the youth and students  in facing the  challenges of the present reality .  This in turn leads ALTERNATIVE ACTION  to identify new development imperatives in preparing the whole country for the fast approaching future.  \r\n<P>\r\nALTERNATIVE ACTION recognizes the important role of the Youth in bridging the lessons of the past to the conduct of the present and to the vision of the future.','[Source:  nrebrochIT.doc brochure sent to info@vote.ph by Alexander E. Casiple]<BR><BR>\r\n<B>OUR LEGISLATIVE AGENDA ON I.T. WILL GUIDED BY THE FOLLOWING DEVELOPMENT THEMES:</B>\r\n<BR>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>Computer and Internet Connectivity in every student’s home.\r\n<LI>Support services for Small Economies in Transition (SET are small and people based enterprises like cooperatives in transition to becoming new economy-compatible.)\r\n<LI>Establishment of Low Interest Adequately Time-spread Credit Facilities for PC acquisition\r\n<LI>Information Technology- enabled Good and Transparent Governance\r\n<LI>Establishment of Community-based Information Technology Centers\r\n<LI>Establishment of Information and Communication Technology Infrastructure in rural Areas.\r\n</UL>','','<P>\r\n<B>Alexander Casiple</B> <BR>\r\nMindanao Campaign Coordinator <BR>\r\nMember, National Board of Governors <BR>','alexedit@hotmail.com','09194230857','','',20010423095856,'','',2001);
